    <descgrp type="add">
      <relatedmaterial>
        <head>Related Material</head>
        <p>These papers augment the Bentley Historical Library's rich holdings documenting the religious history of Southeast Michigan. Researchers interested in the history of Ann Arbor's Zion Lutheran Church should also consult the Zion Lutheran Church records, 1833-1981. This collection contains church history, administrative and financial records, and the papers of church organizations and individual papers. The Bentley Historical Library also holds the records of the Lutheran Church in America, Michigan Synod Records and a number of publications related to Zion Lutheran Church.</p>
      </relatedmaterial>
